#Core Trading Projects in C++17

---

# 1️⃣ Order Matching Engine

### Purpose

Core of any exchange

### Concepts

* `std::priority_queue`
* Price-time priority
* Partial fills

---

# 2️⃣ Market Data Feed Handler

### Purpose

Process live market data (tick-by-tick)

### Concepts

* Streaming data
* Sliding window
* `std::queue`, `std::unordered_map`

---

# 3️⃣ Limit Order Book (Advanced Version)

### Purpose

Maintain full bid/ask book (like real exchange)

### Concepts

* `std::map` / `std::unordered_map`
* Price levels
* Aggregation

Upgrade from your current engine

---

# 4️⃣ Trade Execution Simulator

### Purpose

Simulate order execution strategies

### Concepts

* Strategy pattern
* Latency simulation
* Slippage calculation

---

# 5️⃣ Backtesting Engine

### Purpose

Test trading strategies on historical data

### Concepts

* File I/O optimization
* Data replay
* Performance tuning

---

# 6️⃣ Low Latency Logger

### Purpose

Fast logging without blocking system

### Concepts

* Lock-free queue
* Producer-consumer
* `std::atomic`, `std::thread`

VERY IMPORTANT for trading roles

---

# 7️⃣ Multi-threaded Market Pipeline

### Purpose

Simulate real system pipeline

### Concepts

* Thread 1 → receive data
* Thread 2 → process
* Thread 3 → execute

Use:

* `std::thread`
* `condition_variable`

---

# 8️⃣ Risk Management System

### Purpose

Check if trades are allowed

### Concepts

* Position limits
* Exposure calculation
* Fast lookup (`std::unordered_map`)

---

# 9️⃣ FIX Protocol Simulator (Advanced)

### Purpose

Communicate with exchanges

### Concepts

* String parsing
* Networking (TCP)
* Protocol design

---

# TCP Market Data Server

### Purpose

Send/receive live data over network

### Concepts

* Socket programming
* Async I/O
* Serialization

